WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:00:21.588 --> 00:00:23.852
Why are Warrior Angel
and Black Diamond fighting?

3
00:00:24.024 --> 00:00:26.424
I mean. they're friends.
it doesn't make any sense.

4
00:00:26.593 --> 00:00:28.458
Didn't you read issue 126?

5
00:00:28.628 --> 00:00:31.893
No. I didn't have any money that week.
Why? What happened?

6
00:00:32.065 --> 00:00:35.660
So you know how Black Diamond's father
is like this super villain. right?

7
00:00:35.835 --> 00:00:39.498
Well. in 126. he busts out of jail
and Warrior Angel has to take him down.

8
00:00:39.672 --> 00:00:43.904
But there's this accident
and the guy dies and...

9
00:00:48.681 --> 00:00:50.615
Look who it is. boys.

10
00:00:52.452 --> 00:00:55.580
Weirdo Angel and his trusty sidekick.
Greaspa.

11
00:00:55.755 --> 00:00:57.882
Greaspa. I like that.

12
00:00:58.224 --> 00:00:59.691
Give it back. ollie.

13
00:00:59.859 --> 00:01:02.692
That's Mr. Queen to you. little man.

14
00:01:04.731 --> 00:01:06.961
It's okay. Lex. I'll just get another one.

15
00:01:07.133 --> 00:01:09.499
Yeah. Duncan will just get another one.

16
00:01:09.669 --> 00:01:12.433
Oh. wait. he can't.

17
00:01:12.906 --> 00:01:14.237
Oh. yeah. that's right.

18
00:01:14.407 --> 00:01:16.568
His mommy doesn't have any money.

19
00:01:16.776 --> 00:01:18.869
That's why he's on a scholarship.

20
00:01:19.045 --> 00:01:21.707
Shut up. Geoffrey. Shut up. Alden.

21
00:01:22.515 --> 00:01:24.380
Give it back...

22
00:01:25.485 --> 00:01:26.952
...Mr. Queen.

23
00:01:28.121 --> 00:01:29.645
Sure.

24
00:01:30.090 --> 00:01:31.887
You know what?

25
00:01:32.292 --> 00:01:34.658
- Let's make this a two-parter.
- Don't...

26
00:01:39.966 --> 00:01:41.490
Nice haircut. cue ball.

27
00:01:46.673 --> 00:01:50.109
Come on.
these girls aren't even worth it.

28
00:01:51.478 --> 00:01:53.173
Loser.

29
00:02:05.892 --> 00:02:08.759
One day I'm gonna get those guys.

30
00:02:18.771 --> 00:02:21.968
We had a stuffed crow
at Smallville High.

31
00:02:22.308 --> 00:02:23.502
Two different worlds. huh?

32
00:02:24.244 --> 00:02:27.338
In this case. I think I prefer yours.

33
00:02:30.884 --> 00:02:33.648
If that's how you feel.
why come to this thing?

34
00:02:33.820 --> 00:02:37.449
Lana. some of the deepest pockets
in the country went to Excelsior.

35
00:02:37.624 --> 00:02:40.320
These alumni socials
are good for business.

36
00:02:40.493 --> 00:02:44.293
Well. then let's be social.
so we can get the hell out of here.

37
00:02:44.464 --> 00:02:45.954
Lana.

38
00:02:46.132 --> 00:02:47.895
Your billionaire drag you to this too?

39
00:02:48.902 --> 00:02:49.891
Oliver's here?

40
00:02:50.069 --> 00:02:53.334
I don't get it. You put a bunch
of pubescent boys in silly jackets...

41
00:02:53.506 --> 00:02:55.736
...and cram them full of pomp
and circumstance...

42
00:02:55.909 --> 00:02:58.241
<i>...you're asking for a round
of Lord of the Flies.</i>

43
00:02:58.411 --> 00:03:02.142
I don't know. We all turned out all right.

44
00:03:05.151 --> 00:03:07.483
- Didn't we?
- Hey.

45
00:03:09.389 --> 00:03:12.381
I can only speak for myself.

46
00:03:16.129 --> 00:03:17.756
- Geoffrey. Alden.
- Lex.

47
00:03:17.931 --> 00:03:21.230
- How's business?
- Not as good as you. but hey.

48
00:03:22.735 --> 00:03:25.169
And you guys were all friends?

49
00:03:25.972 --> 00:03:27.030
Something like that.

50
00:03:27.207 --> 00:03:29.198
Man. after 10 years.

51
00:03:30.376 --> 00:03:33.504
- The gang's all here.
- Except for Duncan.

52
00:03:37.884 --> 00:03:39.249
Who's Duncan?

53
00:03:41.688 --> 00:03:44.384
You know what.
maybe you ought to lay off. huh?

54
00:03:44.557 --> 00:03:46.923
- What. you weren't all thinking about it?
- Alden.

55
00:03:47.093 --> 00:03:49.084
Alden. come on.

56
00:03:49.262 --> 00:03:51.457
Yeah. whatever.

57
00:03:52.232 --> 00:03:53.426
Good to see you. Lex.

58
00:03:56.436 --> 00:03:58.495
You did all right for yourself.

59
00:04:10.783 --> 00:04:12.910
Duncan. if you were here...

60
00:04:13.086 --> 00:04:14.781
...you'd still be a loser.

61
00:04:18.324 --> 00:04:20.189
Oh. my God.

62
00:04:26.065 --> 00:04:28.226
- You all right?
- It just missed me.

63
00:04:31.904 --> 00:04:34.134
Must be my lucky day.

64
00:05:39.739 --> 00:05:41.866
I heard what happened.

65
00:05:45.878 --> 00:05:47.812
Are you all right. son?

66
00:05:48.648 --> 00:05:50.673
Nothing a little dry cleaning won't cure.

67
00:05:50.850 --> 00:05:52.442
That's distasteful. Lex.

68
00:05:52.618 --> 00:05:54.051
Even for you.

69
00:05:54.487 --> 00:05:56.478
Well. what can I say?

70
00:05:57.156 --> 00:05:58.145
It's a nice suit.

71
00:06:01.994 --> 00:06:04.326
You weren't Alden's close friend.
Lex. but still...

72
00:06:04.497 --> 00:06:06.522
I should muster up some tears anyway?

73
00:06:08.167 --> 00:06:10.533
Thanks. I'll save them for someone
who deserves it.

74
00:06:13.039 --> 00:06:17.203
I know. I know.
Your life at Excelsior wasn't easy.

75
00:06:19.345 --> 00:06:23.338
And I know that memories can haunt us...

76
00:06:23.516 --> 00:06:26.576
...but the best way to deal with them
is to leave them behind us.

77
00:06:26.753 --> 00:06:29.586
Bury them where they belong...

78
00:06:29.756 --> 00:06:31.417
...in the past.

79
00:06:37.930 --> 00:06:40.364
Along with everything else.

80
00:06:40.533 --> 00:06:41.761
Right. Dad?

81
00:06:44.337 --> 00:06:46.362
I'm glad you're all right.

82
00:06:46.572 --> 00:06:49.234
- Lf you need anything...
- I won't.

83
00:06:57.717 --> 00:07:01.175
Perhaps Miss Lang will have better luck
comforting you.

84
00:07:01.354 --> 00:07:04.482
Would you give her my regards. please?

85
00:07:26.446 --> 00:07:29.847
- What are you gonna do when you get out?
- I don't know. College. I guess.

86
00:07:30.016 --> 00:07:31.005
Then what?

87
00:07:31.184 --> 00:07:33.880
My dad wants me to learn
how to run his business.

88
00:07:34.053 --> 00:07:35.418
Are you gonna do it?

89
00:07:35.988 --> 00:07:37.683
Hell. no.

90
00:07:38.257 --> 00:07:40.623
I can't stand that old bastard.

91
00:07:42.028 --> 00:07:44.428
What about you?
What are you gonna do?

92
00:07:45.731 --> 00:07:47.756
I'm gonna help people.
like Warrior Angel.

93
00:07:48.901 --> 00:07:51.631
Better hit the gym.
Spandex is tough to pull off.

94
00:07:51.804 --> 00:07:55.296
No. I don't mean like the cape and stuff.

95
00:07:55.475 --> 00:07:58.205
I'm talking like a doctor or a lawyer
or something.

96
00:07:59.312 --> 00:08:01.337
- Lawyer.
- Yeah.

97
00:08:01.514 --> 00:08:03.277
Working pro bono for the poor.

98
00:08:04.450 --> 00:08:06.145
Don't let my dad hear you say that.

99
00:08:06.719 --> 00:08:08.812
Why? What's your dad
got against poor people?

100
00:08:08.988 --> 00:08:10.683
Everything.

101
00:08:10.957 --> 00:08:16.156
- He thinks poverty is another word for lazy.
- What do you think?

102
00:08:19.966 --> 00:08:24.733
I think it would drive my dad nuts
if I got a job working with the poor.

103
00:08:25.638 --> 00:08:27.299
Got room for a partner?

104
00:08:29.041 --> 00:08:30.633
Allenmeyer and Luthor?

105
00:08:31.844 --> 00:08:33.209
Luthor and Allenmeyer.

106
00:08:33.746 --> 00:08:35.338
Deal.

107
00:08:41.487 --> 00:08:44.081
Now all we gotta do
is graduate in one piece.

108
00:08:44.257 --> 00:08:45.849
Come on.

109
00:08:46.025 --> 00:08:47.652
Hurry.

110
00:08:48.294 --> 00:08:51.161
- Did you get it?
- I got it.

111
00:08:51.330 --> 00:08:52.957
Let's go.

112
00:08:53.132 --> 00:08:55.498
Oh. man. this is too cool.

113
00:08:56.302 --> 00:08:59.066
- Sweet.
- Nobody saw us.

114
00:09:00.439 --> 00:09:02.407
Awesome.

115
00:09:08.281 --> 00:09:09.976
What are they doing?

116
00:09:10.149 --> 00:09:13.744
Stealing answers to the midterms.

117
00:09:26.332 --> 00:09:28.732
You didn't have to go
to all this trouble. Mrs. Kent.

118
00:09:28.901 --> 00:09:31.893
You can't live on coffee
three meals a day. Chloe.

119
00:09:32.071 --> 00:09:34.733
I mix it up with the occasional
blueberry muffin.

120
00:09:35.341 --> 00:09:38.674
- What? That has a food group in it.
- Barely.

121
00:09:38.945 --> 00:09:41.778
- So you find anything new?
- Tons.

122
00:09:41.948 --> 00:09:45.247
There've been reports of unusual
occurrences all over the world.

123
00:09:45.418 --> 00:09:48.080
It's like the Wall of Weird
went global.

124
00:09:48.254 --> 00:09:51.348
The worst attack was on a village
in the Kashmir region of India.

125
00:09:51.524 --> 00:09:53.458
The entire village
was nearly destroyed.

126
00:09:57.196 --> 00:10:00.131
They saw something fall
from the sky the night before.

127
00:10:02.168 --> 00:10:04.568
That's the same time I escaped
from the Phantom Zone.

128
00:10:06.606 --> 00:10:08.972
You think whatever it was
got out when you escaped?

129
00:10:09.141 --> 00:10:11.473
Like that park ranger.

130
00:10:11.644 --> 00:10:13.236
How about a trip to the ice castle?

131
00:10:13.412 --> 00:10:16.575
Maybe Jor-El could help track the Zoners
before they do more damage.

132
00:10:16.983 --> 00:10:17.972
Zoners?

133
00:10:19.385 --> 00:10:22.582
Escaped super criminals from the
Phantom Zone's a bit of a mouthful.

134
00:10:22.755 --> 00:10:27.624
The Fortress is dead. There's no way
to contact Jor-El and ask for his help.

135
00:10:27.860 --> 00:10:30.761
- I should have just listened to him.
- And done what. Clark?

136
00:10:30.930 --> 00:10:34.024
Killed Lex to stop Zod
from taking over his body?

137
00:10:34.200 --> 00:10:36.532
You're not a murderer. Clark.

138
00:10:36.702 --> 00:10:38.727
What about those people
in that village. Mom?

139
00:10:38.904 --> 00:10:42.340
They might have died because
of my actions. I need to know for sure.

140
00:10:45.911 --> 00:10:47.936
Then we need to find
more crater impacts...

141
00:10:49.315 --> 00:10:51.840
...like the one you made
when you came out of the Zone.

142
00:10:52.018 --> 00:10:54.145
I think our best bet
would be satellite images.

143
00:10:54.320 --> 00:10:56.550
I thought satellites were down
on Dark Thursday?

144
00:10:56.722 --> 00:10:59.555
All except for a few
owned by Queen Industries.

145
00:10:59.725 --> 00:11:02.956
If we could get the access codes.
I might be able to find an image...

146
00:11:03.129 --> 00:11:06.895
...of whatever it is that came down
before the attack on that village.

147
00:11:07.066 --> 00:11:09.660
Oliver Queen still owes me one.

148
00:11:10.336 --> 00:11:13.032
Maybe it's time to collect.

149
00:11:16.308 --> 00:11:20.836
Seeing somebody you laughed with.
shared so many good times together...

150
00:11:21.414 --> 00:11:24.042
Seeing them laid out on a table like that...

151
00:11:24.684 --> 00:11:26.345
At least they say he didn't suffer.

152
00:11:26.519 --> 00:11:29.079
Yeah. But I'm guessing
it didn't tickle either.

153
00:11:29.255 --> 00:11:31.723
You know. Alden called me a month ago.

154
00:11:31.991 --> 00:11:34.152
Said he wanted to go out
for a drink and I...

155
00:11:36.962 --> 00:11:40.261
I told him I was busy.
Said I'd catch up with him later.

156
00:11:40.433 --> 00:11:42.594
You couldn't have known
this was gonna happen.

157
00:11:44.103 --> 00:11:48.597
All the more reason to live for today.
Keep in touch with old friends?

158
00:11:51.610 --> 00:11:54.545
Why don't you all get together
while you're here?

159
00:11:56.449 --> 00:11:58.610
What about Duncan.
does he live in Metropolis?

160
00:12:04.957 --> 00:12:09.485
- Not anymore.
- I have to be getting back to Gotham.

161
00:12:11.263 --> 00:12:13.197
You got a great gal there. ollie.

162
00:12:13.365 --> 00:12:15.026
Don't screw it up.

163
00:12:47.099 --> 00:12:50.000
Smart guy. You should listen to him.

164
00:12:50.169 --> 00:12:51.761
I'm all ears.

165
00:13:29.608 --> 00:13:30.666
Clark.

166
00:13:31.443 --> 00:13:33.911
I was wondering if my system
would keep you out.

167
00:13:34.814 --> 00:13:37.783
- Looks like you need an upgrade.
- Or you need to learn to knock.

168
00:13:39.018 --> 00:13:42.215
It's okay. You know what? You can keep
that arrow. I've got a new one.

169
00:13:45.191 --> 00:13:47.955
I was thinking about a boxing-glove arrow.
then I thought:

170
00:13:48.127 --> 00:13:49.560
"Something a little fancier."

171
00:14:07.513 --> 00:14:09.276
Contained electromagnetic pulse.

172
00:14:09.448 --> 00:14:12.042
Knocks out everything electrical
within an 8-foot radius.

173
00:14:12.218 --> 00:14:16.211
Cameras. laser systems. pacemakers.

174
00:14:16.789 --> 00:14:18.654
The last one was a joke. Clark.

175
00:14:20.359 --> 00:14:21.849
I'm laughing on the inside.

176
00:14:22.461 --> 00:14:25.328
Maybe we'll get lucky one day
and it'll bubble to the surface.

177
00:14:25.497 --> 00:14:28.557
- To what do I owe the pleasure?
- To talk about Queen Industries.

178
00:14:28.734 --> 00:14:30.531
Their satellite grid.

179
00:14:31.203 --> 00:14:32.192
What about it?

180
00:14:33.372 --> 00:14:37.172
My friend Chloe. she's doing a story
on the global effects of Dark Thursday.

181
00:14:37.343 --> 00:14:40.608
She needs satellite images from that day.
but none were working.

182
00:14:40.779 --> 00:14:41.768
Except mine.

183
00:14:42.481 --> 00:14:43.709
Now. how'd you manage that?

184
00:14:44.617 --> 00:14:45.914
It's a trade secret.

185
00:14:46.085 --> 00:14:47.712
Tell you what...

186
00:14:48.587 --> 00:14:51.112
...l'll give Chloe the access codes
to the archive...

187
00:14:51.290 --> 00:14:52.882
...if you do one thing for me.

188
00:14:54.059 --> 00:14:55.048
What would that be?

189
00:14:55.227 --> 00:14:59.561
Help me figure out how Lex caused
the accidental death of two of my friends.

190
00:15:00.933 --> 00:15:02.457
You think Lex killed them?

191
00:15:02.635 --> 00:15:05.570
I've known Lex
a lot longer than you. Clark.

192
00:15:06.305 --> 00:15:09.274
I've seen who he really is.

193
00:15:16.715 --> 00:15:20.116
- I'm just saying we should think about this.
- What's there to think about?

194
00:15:20.286 --> 00:15:23.949
We tell the headmaster what we saw
and Queen and those jerks are out of here.

195
00:15:24.123 --> 00:15:26.990
But we have something on Queen now.

196
00:15:28.060 --> 00:15:30.927
No way is he ever gonna
try anything again.

197
00:15:32.831 --> 00:15:34.890
We can use this.

198
00:15:35.067 --> 00:15:39.265
Force him to act like our friend
so we can have some respect in this place.

199
00:15:41.707 --> 00:15:45.609
You don't pretend
to be friends with somebody. Lex.

200
00:15:45.778 --> 00:15:47.507
You either are or you aren't.

201
00:15:50.849 --> 00:15:52.817
I'm gonna turn them in.

202
00:15:55.554 --> 00:15:57.920
I thought you said
you were gonna handle this.

203
00:16:06.165 --> 00:16:08.599
You told them?

204
00:16:09.401 --> 00:16:11.631
This is our chance. Duncan.

205
00:16:11.804 --> 00:16:15.171
We don't have to be
on the outside anymore.

206
00:16:18.077 --> 00:16:21.376
I never felt that way.
not when you were my friend.

207
00:16:21.981 --> 00:16:24.211
- Just listen to me.
- Get out of my way.

208
00:16:26.352 --> 00:16:29.412
Hey. where do you think you're going?

209
00:16:29.588 --> 00:16:32.079
Just keep your mouth shut
and everything will be okay.

210
00:16:32.257 --> 00:16:34.589
Get off of me.

211
00:16:39.765 --> 00:16:42.393
Get him. right on.
Get him. cue ball.

212
00:16:43.469 --> 00:16:45.562
Why do you have to be such a loser?

213
00:16:46.038 --> 00:16:48.131
Why can't you be like everybody else?

214
00:16:50.642 --> 00:16:52.439
Are you okay?

215
00:16:53.212 --> 00:16:54.679
Yeah.

216
00:16:54.847 --> 00:16:56.405
Bad dream.

217
00:16:56.882 --> 00:16:58.349
What was it about?

218
00:16:58.517 --> 00:17:00.644
I don't remember.

219
00:17:01.587 --> 00:17:05.887
Lex. it's normal to be upset.
Alden died right in front of you.

220
00:17:06.058 --> 00:17:08.322
Yeah. well. maybe he finally
got what he deserved.

221
00:17:09.228 --> 00:17:11.662
How can you say that about your friend?

222
00:17:13.732 --> 00:17:16.326
I only had one friend at Excelsior.

223
00:17:16.502 --> 00:17:18.732
And it sure as hell wasn't him.

224
00:17:19.171 --> 00:17:20.934
Do you wanna talk about it?

225
00:17:24.376 --> 00:17:26.207
Not really.

226
00:17:27.646 --> 00:17:29.705
Lana. I'm all right.

227
00:17:29.882 --> 00:17:32.077
I'm the last thing
you have to worry about.

228
00:17:44.930 --> 00:17:47.091
The last thing. huh?

229
00:17:48.834 --> 00:17:51.064
Well. at least it didn't break.

230
00:18:01.013 --> 00:18:02.412
Did you see that?

231
00:18:03.182 --> 00:18:05.946
I'm sure it's nothing
to worry about. Lana.

232
00:18:17.029 --> 00:18:18.690
See?

233
00:18:23.001 --> 00:18:24.491
Lex.

234
00:18:28.140 --> 00:18:29.903
Lana!

235
00:18:33.712 --> 00:18:35.680
Lana?

236
00:18:39.585 --> 00:18:41.485
Lana.

237
00:18:50.629 --> 00:18:53.723
She sustained a serious concussion.
but the CAT scans are negative.

238
00:18:53.899 --> 00:18:57.960
- Couple of days of rest and she'll be fine.
- I'll make sure she gets it.

239
00:19:00.939 --> 00:19:02.497
- Where's Lana?
- She'll be fine.

240
00:19:02.674 --> 00:19:05.336
- That's the only thing that matters.
- I wanna talk to her.

241
00:19:06.245 --> 00:19:08.543
You lost your visiting rights
a while back. Clark.

242
00:19:12.651 --> 00:19:15.142
I wouldn't be here
if it wasn't for you. Lex.

243
00:19:15.320 --> 00:19:18.016
Since you've been with her
she has a habit of getting hurt.

244
00:19:18.190 --> 00:19:22.126
And how many times did she wind up
in the hospital when she was dating you?

245
00:19:32.504 --> 00:19:34.938
Save yourself the trip next time. Clark.

246
00:19:35.107 --> 00:19:37.337
Just send flowers.

247
00:19:42.314 --> 00:19:43.303
That was harsh.

248
00:19:45.350 --> 00:19:47.443
It's not like he's wrong. though.

249
00:19:48.153 --> 00:19:51.748
I've hurt Lana more than anyone. She
wouldn't be with Lex if it wasn't for me.

250
00:19:51.924 --> 00:19:54.017
Lana made that questionable choice
on her own.

251
00:19:54.193 --> 00:19:57.356
Stop beating yourself up.
That's my job.

252
00:19:58.430 --> 00:20:00.591
And my other one
is sniffing out a good story.

253
00:20:01.366 --> 00:20:02.526
That's why you're here?

254
00:20:02.701 --> 00:20:06.296
I don't think Lana's chandelier run-in
was an accident...

255
00:20:06.471 --> 00:20:08.302
...or that she was the target.

256
00:20:08.473 --> 00:20:11.237
In the past 24 hours.
two of Lex and oliver's old friends...

257
00:20:11.410 --> 00:20:14.504
...from boarding school
died in violent accidents.

258
00:20:14.980 --> 00:20:17.210
And you think Lex was almost the third?

259
00:20:17.382 --> 00:20:20.374
It has something to do
with a kid named Duncan they all knew...

260
00:20:20.552 --> 00:20:22.281
...but oliver won't tell me anything.

261
00:20:23.655 --> 00:20:26.453
I don't want you to end up
sharing a hospital room with Lana.

262
00:20:26.625 --> 00:20:29.059
Get some distance
between you and oliver for now.

263
00:20:29.228 --> 00:20:33.062
Or I could man up and get
to the bottom of this like a real reporter.

264
00:20:33.232 --> 00:20:37.726
Preferably before the Grim Reaper drops
something very heavy on my hot boyfriend.

265
00:20:49.047 --> 00:20:51.072
Is Lana gonna be okay?

266
00:20:51.750 --> 00:20:53.012
I think so.

267
00:20:53.185 --> 00:20:56.518
Looks like you were wrong about Lex
being the one behind the attacks.

268
00:20:56.688 --> 00:20:59.987
Unless he orchestrated this one
to throw off suspicion.

269
00:21:00.792 --> 00:21:04.057
If Lex was the only one hurt.
then I'd probably think the same thing.

270
00:21:05.063 --> 00:21:08.055
But he loves Lana too much
to risk her life.

271
00:21:12.437 --> 00:21:14.064
Look. these attacks aren't random.

272
00:21:19.745 --> 00:21:23.579
Lois seems to think it may have something
to do with the kid back at Excelsior.

273
00:21:23.749 --> 00:21:25.341
Duncan?

274
00:21:27.352 --> 00:21:30.617
- It's not Duncan.
- How can you be sure?

275
00:21:36.361 --> 00:21:38.921
Because Lex and I killed him
10 years ago.

276
00:21:39.531 --> 00:21:41.158
Why do you have to be such a loser?

277
00:21:41.333 --> 00:21:42.664
- Lex. stop it.
- That's enough.

278
00:21:42.834 --> 00:21:44.495
Lex. stop it. What are you doing?

279
00:21:44.670 --> 00:21:46.297
Come on. stop.

280
00:21:52.377 --> 00:21:55.312
- Dude.
- Psycho much?

281
00:21:57.349 --> 00:22:00.318
There's something seriously
wrong with you.

282
00:22:14.533 --> 00:22:17.024
- Duncan.
- Get away from me.

283
00:22:20.672 --> 00:22:23.732
You wanna be
one of them so badly. Lex?

284
00:22:25.711 --> 00:22:30.307
Is that it? You can't stand
being a loser like me?

285
00:22:30.649 --> 00:22:33.550
Well. congratulations. buddy.
Now you're their friend.

286
00:22:33.719 --> 00:22:34.981
And you can now all...

287
00:22:35.887 --> 00:22:37.752
Duncan!

288
00:22:38.023 --> 00:22:39.820
Oh. my God.

289
00:22:46.264 --> 00:22:48.323
Duncan suffered massive brain injuries.

290
00:22:48.500 --> 00:22:51.958
Is there anything else
that you haven't told me?

291
00:22:54.439 --> 00:22:56.407
Just the d�nouement.

292
00:22:56.975 --> 00:23:01.275
Lionel Luthor sweeping in with the best
doctors in the world to save Duncan.

293
00:23:02.080 --> 00:23:03.069
Lionel.

294
00:23:04.483 --> 00:23:06.883
I thought it was an act of kindness.

295
00:23:07.252 --> 00:23:10.244
Now that I'm older.
I realize it was just an act.

296
00:23:10.722 --> 00:23:13.919
Lionel was trying to cover up
what happened between Lex and Duncan.

297
00:23:14.459 --> 00:23:17.519
Trying to cover up the stink
off the Luthor name.

298
00:23:17.896 --> 00:23:20.262
How did he know about all this?

299
00:23:21.733 --> 00:23:24.327
He got the whole story from Lex.

300
00:23:27.472 --> 00:23:29.133
Duncan was on scholarship.

301
00:23:29.307 --> 00:23:33.107
His parents couldn't afford a Band-Aid.
let alone a team of neurosurgeons.

302
00:23:33.278 --> 00:23:35.746
So Lionel promised to take care
of the whole thing.

303
00:23:36.681 --> 00:23:39.275
- As long as everyone kept quiet.
- Not that it mattered.

304
00:23:39.718 --> 00:23:41.948
Duncan died two days later.

305
00:23:44.823 --> 00:23:46.757
It was an accident.

306
00:23:46.925 --> 00:23:48.449
It just happened.

307
00:23:49.928 --> 00:23:51.327
No.

308
00:23:51.496 --> 00:23:54.465
No. I told myself that same lie for years.

309
00:23:56.001 --> 00:23:59.334
Truth is. all of us might as well
have pushed him in front of that car.

310
00:23:59.504 --> 00:24:02.905
Alden. Geoffrey. Lex. me.

311
00:24:03.208 --> 00:24:05.506
We all killed Duncan Allenmeyer.

312
00:24:19.090 --> 00:24:20.455
What about his family?

313
00:24:20.625 --> 00:24:23.025
If you killed him.
one of them might be behind this.

314
00:24:23.195 --> 00:24:25.959
But the only relative
I could find was his mother.

315
00:24:26.465 --> 00:24:29.229
- Where's she?
- Granville Cemetery.

316
00:24:29.401 --> 00:24:31.266
She passed away a month ago.

317
00:24:33.104 --> 00:24:35.595
Well. there must be someone else
you may have missed.

318
00:24:35.774 --> 00:24:37.298
I don't know.

319
00:24:38.810 --> 00:24:42.439
The only one who had contact
with Duncan's family was Lionel.

320
00:24:42.614 --> 00:24:44.445
I'm not exactly high
on his buddy list.

321
00:24:44.616 --> 00:24:46.709
Not a good chance of him talking to me.

322
00:25:02.934 --> 00:25:08.395
I was just on my way down the street
to Pastis for lunch.

323
00:25:08.573 --> 00:25:11.007
- You hungry?
- No. this isn't a social visit.

324
00:25:11.176 --> 00:25:12.165
Oh. that's a pity.

325
00:25:12.344 --> 00:25:17.338
The owner's wife does
a souffl� au fromage that is...

326
00:25:17.516 --> 00:25:19.848
Well. it is out of this world.

327
00:25:20.018 --> 00:25:22.009
Duncan Allenmeyer.

328
00:25:26.358 --> 00:25:27.848
How do you know that name?

329
00:25:28.026 --> 00:25:29.687
Oliver Queen filled me in.

330
00:25:29.861 --> 00:25:32.728
Oh. yes. the Queen boy.

331
00:25:32.898 --> 00:25:35.264
He should know better
than to dig up old skeletons.

332
00:25:35.433 --> 00:25:38.300
I'm not sure he's the only one
with a shovel in his hand.

333
00:25:39.471 --> 00:25:43.407
These attacks. I think someone who was
close to Duncan is trying to settle the score.

334
00:25:44.075 --> 00:25:45.702
Lex was the only one close to him.

335
00:25:45.877 --> 00:25:48.277
No other family members
besides his mother?

336
00:25:48.914 --> 00:25:51.280
- He didn't have any.
- There's gotta be someone.

337
00:25:54.819 --> 00:25:56.377
What is it you're not telling me?

338
00:25:57.255 --> 00:26:00.053
- Clark...
- Two people are already dead.

339
00:26:00.859 --> 00:26:02.588
Do you wanna add Lex
to the body count?

340
00:26:04.596 --> 00:26:06.427
Now. please. tell me.

341
00:26:12.704 --> 00:26:16.299
It was a tragedy.
what happened to Duncan.

342
00:26:16.474 --> 00:26:19.136
I did everything possible to help him.

343
00:26:22.380 --> 00:26:26.248
I have continued to do that
for the past 10 years.

344
00:26:26.751 --> 00:26:28.241
Duncan's alive?

345
00:26:28.853 --> 00:26:32.152
My medical team was able
to keep his heart beating.

346
00:26:33.325 --> 00:26:38.422
But the injuries from his accident have
left him in a permanent vegetative state.

347
00:26:40.332 --> 00:26:42.664
Why did you let everyone believe
he was still dead?

348
00:26:46.738 --> 00:26:48.262
Clark...

349
00:26:52.010 --> 00:26:55.946
...I didn't want Lex to be crippled
by his mistakes.

350
00:26:56.114 --> 00:26:59.550
I decided to make an arrangement
with Duncan's mother...

351
00:26:59.718 --> 00:27:03.313
...in exchange for her silence.
going along with the story...

352
00:27:04.155 --> 00:27:08.854
...I agreed to fund a research program...

353
00:27:09.794 --> 00:27:13.457
...dedicated to reversing the damage
to her son's brain.

354
00:27:14.799 --> 00:27:16.892
This is still going on.

355
00:27:18.203 --> 00:27:23.163
The best research minds in the world have
tried hundreds of different treatments. but...

356
00:27:23.341 --> 00:27:25.309
What if one of them worked?

357
00:28:05.250 --> 00:28:07.980
It's time for your treatment. Duncan.

358
00:28:30.709 --> 00:28:32.540
Smallville?

359
00:28:32.977 --> 00:28:34.467
Lois. what are you doing here?

360
00:28:34.646 --> 00:28:37.046
I'm following a lead.
I checked out Duncan's mother.

361
00:28:37.215 --> 00:28:39.740
- She's dead.
- I know that. Sherlock.

362
00:28:39.918 --> 00:28:42.113
On a hunch. I dug up
all her old phone records.

363
00:28:42.287 --> 00:28:45.279
Every day. while she was still kicking.
she called this facility.

364
00:28:45.457 --> 00:28:47.448
She was checking on her son.

365
00:28:47.625 --> 00:28:49.991
Duncan? I thought he was dead.

366
00:28:50.161 --> 00:28:52.288
Yeah. so did everyone else.

367
00:28:52.464 --> 00:28:56.696
- I think he's in this room.
- How do you know all this?

368
00:28:57.535 --> 00:29:00.800
- You're not the only one with hunches.
- Nice work.

369
00:29:01.406 --> 00:29:03.533
Lois?

370
00:29:09.581 --> 00:29:11.549
It's my story. I don't share bylines.

371
00:29:13.985 --> 00:29:18.149
It's locked. You stay here.
I'm gonna flirt us up a set of keys. all right?

372
00:29:22.160 --> 00:29:24.060
Lois.

373
00:29:24.462 --> 00:29:25.929
It was just stuck.

374
00:29:27.432 --> 00:29:30.424
Fine. Ladies first.

375
00:29:40.078 --> 00:29:41.136
Yes?

376
00:29:41.312 --> 00:29:43.439
<i>He's arriving now. Mr. Queen.</i>

377
00:29:43.615 --> 00:29:45.014
Thank you.

378
00:29:51.356 --> 00:29:54.484
Lex. I was wondering how long
it was gonna take you to pop up.

379
00:29:55.560 --> 00:29:59.291
I've been busy at the hospital.

380
00:29:59.597 --> 00:30:00.859
I heard about Lana.

381
00:30:01.032 --> 00:30:04.001
- Is she gonna be all right?
- She'll be fine.

382
00:30:04.169 --> 00:30:05.796
Not that you really care.

383
00:30:05.970 --> 00:30:07.961
No. I do care.

384
00:30:08.840 --> 00:30:11.968
I care that a nice girl like that
ended up with a guy like you.

385
00:30:14.546 --> 00:30:17.845
Ever since you came to Metropolis.
I've been kidnapped...

386
00:30:18.016 --> 00:30:19.347
...my life put in jeopardy...

387
00:30:19.517 --> 00:30:22.111
...and now the woman I love
is lying in a hospital bed.

388
00:30:22.320 --> 00:30:24.550
And you think that's my fault.

389
00:30:25.657 --> 00:30:27.386
Sounds to me more like bad karma.

390
00:30:28.960 --> 00:30:31.827
Go back to Star City. oliver...

391
00:30:32.230 --> 00:30:34.027
...while you still can.

392
00:30:35.667 --> 00:30:37.794
I've seen that look before.

393
00:30:39.170 --> 00:30:40.899
When was it?

394
00:30:42.473 --> 00:30:44.065
Oh. yeah.

395
00:30:45.009 --> 00:30:48.877
When you almost beat your only friend
to death back at Excelsior.

396
00:30:59.057 --> 00:31:00.046
That's good.

397
00:31:01.526 --> 00:31:04.689
The first one's free.
The next one's gonna cost you.

398
00:31:10.268 --> 00:31:11.633
Poor little Lex.

399
00:31:11.803 --> 00:31:14.431
Always blaming everyone else
for all of his problems.

400
00:31:14.606 --> 00:31:16.801
Only when they're the cause.

401
00:31:22.914 --> 00:31:25.576
You never could take responsibility
for what happened.

402
00:31:25.750 --> 00:31:27.411
Like your hands were clean?

403
00:31:28.853 --> 00:31:30.184
Not even close.

404
00:31:30.355 --> 00:31:32.789
But since then.
I've been scrubbing them real hard.

405
00:31:32.957 --> 00:31:34.447
Yours just keep getting dirtier.

406
00:31:49.908 --> 00:31:50.897
Lex.

407
00:32:16.668 --> 00:32:19.228
I'm not a doctor. but I've seen
enough to know...

408
00:32:19.404 --> 00:32:22.430
...you don't get squiggly lines
when you're in a vegetative state.

409
00:32:22.607 --> 00:32:25.440
Unless your new treatments are working.

410
00:32:25.810 --> 00:32:27.368
What new treatment?

411
00:32:27.545 --> 00:32:31.072
Something called 12B. It's experimental.

412
00:32:31.249 --> 00:32:33.308
It's derived from refined meteor rocks.

413
00:32:33.751 --> 00:32:37.414
Clark. they started giving him this stuff
two days ago.

414
00:32:37.588 --> 00:32:40.580
- Look at the injection times.
- They coincide with the attacks.

415
00:32:41.626 --> 00:32:43.321
Maybe we just found our killer.

416
00:32:43.895 --> 00:32:47.626
Wait. these treatments might stimulate
brain activity. but he's in a wheelchair.

417
00:32:47.799 --> 00:32:50.529
His body is. yeah. But look at his charts.

418
00:32:50.702 --> 00:32:54.035
His new cocktail is whipping up
a hell of an electrical storm.

419
00:32:54.205 --> 00:32:58.164
<i>I read this article in The Inquisitor
about brain waves and astral projection.</i>

420
00:32:58.343 --> 00:32:59.674
Astral projection?

421
00:33:00.712 --> 00:33:02.270
Do you have a better explanation?

422
00:33:03.414 --> 00:33:06.850
No. When was his last injection?

423
00:33:07.752 --> 00:33:08.844
Twenty minutes ago.

424
00:33:12.056 --> 00:33:14.889
Oh. my God. It's happening again.

425
00:33:15.059 --> 00:33:16.754
Smallville. l...

426
00:34:14.252 --> 00:34:15.685
Hey.

427
00:34:15.853 --> 00:34:16.877
What happened?

428
00:34:17.288 --> 00:34:19.722
You went AWoL while things heated up.
as usual.

429
00:34:20.425 --> 00:34:23.394
I went to go find a phone
to warn oliver and Lex.

430
00:34:24.362 --> 00:34:26.557
Did you get ahold of them?
Are they all right?

431
00:34:26.731 --> 00:34:30.064
A little worse for wear. Oliver said
whatever happened suddenly stopped.

432
00:34:30.535 --> 00:34:32.867
Well. Duncan went flatline.
like he blew a fuse.

433
00:34:34.405 --> 00:34:36.896
I wonder what caused it.

434
00:34:37.075 --> 00:34:38.804
You need that for your article?

435
00:34:38.976 --> 00:34:42.104
Well. it would be good.
if I were still going to write one.

436
00:34:42.280 --> 00:34:43.406
But you're not?

437
00:34:43.915 --> 00:34:47.112
<i>It would make a juicy story
for The Inquisitor.</i>

438
00:34:47.285 --> 00:34:50.743
But considering the outcome.
an exploitation piece...

439
00:34:50.922 --> 00:34:54.289
...on a catatonic patient
astral-projecting his way to revenge...

440
00:34:54.459 --> 00:34:56.586
...might be in bad taste.

441
00:34:57.495 --> 00:34:59.963
Would you feel the same way
if oliver wasn't involved?

442
00:35:01.199 --> 00:35:03.064
We've all done things
we're not proud of.

443
00:35:03.234 --> 00:35:05.464
I just wish oliver didn't feel
he had to hide it.

444
00:35:07.138 --> 00:35:08.469
You know...

445
00:35:10.741 --> 00:35:14.142
...sometimes. in order to protect
the people we love...

446
00:35:14.579 --> 00:35:16.911
...we keep secrets.

447
00:35:18.749 --> 00:35:20.478
That is...

448
00:35:20.718 --> 00:35:22.948
...totally retarded.

449
00:35:36.567 --> 00:35:39.934
I wasn't the most popular kid
at Excelsior.

450
00:35:40.138 --> 00:35:41.765
The way I looked...

451
00:35:42.340 --> 00:35:45.741
The rumors about what happened
to my brother. Julian...

452
00:35:46.677 --> 00:35:48.702
But Duncan didn't care.

453
00:35:49.480 --> 00:35:51.846
He was my only friend.

454
00:35:53.151 --> 00:35:55.051
And I betrayed him.

455
00:35:56.287 --> 00:35:58.653
Lex. you were just a boy.

456
00:35:59.090 --> 00:36:01.524
What matters is the man you've become.

457
00:36:14.038 --> 00:36:15.869
You're early.

458
00:36:16.607 --> 00:36:19.633
It's not often I get invited
into the lion's den.

459
00:36:19.810 --> 00:36:21.539
I didn't want you changing your mind.

460
00:36:22.380 --> 00:36:25.372
I'm sure you two have a lot to discuss.

461
00:36:26.050 --> 00:36:27.312
Mr. Queen.

462
00:36:27.985 --> 00:36:29.577
Miss Lang.

463
00:36:31.222 --> 00:36:32.689
You're a lucky man.

464
00:36:34.091 --> 00:36:36.286
In more ways than one.

465
00:36:39.630 --> 00:36:41.621
I should be dead...

466
00:36:42.667 --> 00:36:43.929
...but here I stand.

467
00:36:44.402 --> 00:36:47.337
Well. you would have done
the same thing for me...

468
00:36:47.572 --> 00:36:48.561
...right?

469
00:36:48.739 --> 00:36:50.969
I wanted to say thank you.

470
00:36:51.976 --> 00:36:54.308
And that's all I wanted to say.

471
00:36:54.946 --> 00:36:57.346
I'm sure you have business
to get back to.

472
00:36:58.282 --> 00:36:59.442
Lex.

473
00:37:07.558 --> 00:37:09.719
What happened to Duncan...

474
00:37:11.295 --> 00:37:13.695
...the way I treated both of you...

475
00:37:16.267 --> 00:37:17.962
...it's not something I'm proud of.

476
00:37:21.105 --> 00:37:23.471
I want you to know how much I regret it.

477
00:37:30.848 --> 00:37:36.115
And I regret ever thinking
I needed friends like you.

478
00:37:58.843 --> 00:38:00.868
Why'd you lie to me?

479
00:38:01.646 --> 00:38:04.911
All those years. you let me think
he was dead.

480
00:38:06.651 --> 00:38:09.051
What would you have done
if you had known the truth?

481
00:38:09.220 --> 00:38:11.984
Make daily pilgrimages
to the poor boy's bedside?

482
00:38:12.623 --> 00:38:15.490
Yes. I let you think he was dead.

483
00:38:15.660 --> 00:38:19.027
I was giving you a chance
to move on with your life.

484
00:38:19.196 --> 00:38:23.064
- To go forward. not back.
- You didn't do this for me.

485
00:38:23.567 --> 00:38:27.333
You convinced Duncan's mother
so you could use him as a guinea pig.

486
00:38:27.505 --> 00:38:31.498
And one of your treatments tapped into
a very powerful part of the human brain.

487
00:38:32.143 --> 00:38:35.840
All right. Let's assume that's true.
Would that have made a difference?

488
00:38:36.013 --> 00:38:38.880
You were responsible for what happened
to Duncan Allenmeyer.

489
00:38:40.051 --> 00:38:42.576
Nothing is ever gonna change that.

490
00:38:44.955 --> 00:38:46.115
Like you said. Dad.

491
00:38:48.559 --> 00:38:50.857
The only thing I can do is look forward.

492
00:38:54.031 --> 00:38:57.558
I wanna see the data
on Duncan's last treatment.

493
00:38:57.868 --> 00:39:00.735
Have it on my desk
first thing in the morning.

494
00:39:10.314 --> 00:39:14.114
So that thing that attacked us. Duncan's
astral body. or whatever you call it...

495
00:39:14.285 --> 00:39:16.480
...must have been
electrical manifestation.

496
00:39:16.654 --> 00:39:18.986
Yeah. he got fried
by your electromagnetic arrow...

497
00:39:19.156 --> 00:39:21.920
...along with what was left
of Duncan's brain.

498
00:39:23.861 --> 00:39:25.089
Yeah. I guess you're right.

499
00:39:28.332 --> 00:39:31.529
You know. making the wrong choices
and living with the consequences...

500
00:39:31.702 --> 00:39:32.828
...it's not easy. is it?

501
00:39:34.238 --> 00:39:35.933
Speaking from experience. huh?

502
00:39:36.841 --> 00:39:38.570
More than I'd like.

503
00:39:45.015 --> 00:39:46.448
We all make bad choices. Clark.

504
00:39:46.617 --> 00:39:49.313
All we can do is hope
to make the right ones in the future.

505
00:39:52.523 --> 00:39:54.354
Clark.

506
00:39:55.226 --> 00:39:57.524
I'm sorry.
I didn't realize you had company.

507
00:39:58.362 --> 00:39:59.886
Chloe. oliver Queen.

508
00:40:01.832 --> 00:40:03.925
Hi. I feel like I know you already.

509
00:40:04.101 --> 00:40:05.762
Lois talks about you all the time.

510
00:40:06.137 --> 00:40:08.935
I was actually just gonna go
see Lois right now.

511
00:40:09.106 --> 00:40:11.734
Maybe it's time I did some talking.

512
00:40:12.309 --> 00:40:15.073
Well. I'm looking forward
to your article on Dark Thursday.

513
00:40:19.150 --> 00:40:22.313
- I hope my satellite images helped.
- Yeah.

514
00:40:22.720 --> 00:40:23.778
Good.

515
00:40:23.954 --> 00:40:25.444
It was good to meet you.

516
00:40:26.157 --> 00:40:27.488
Clark.

517
00:40:32.229 --> 00:40:33.958
In person. he is really...

518
00:40:38.736 --> 00:40:42.137
Chloe. Were you able
to pull anything off the satellites?

519
00:40:42.673 --> 00:40:45.767
Oh. yeah. Well. I'm still sifting
through the images...

520
00:40:45.943 --> 00:40:49.572
...but I already found a handful of craters
that matched the one you made...

521
00:40:49.747 --> 00:40:51.374
...when you busted
out of the Zone.

522
00:40:52.516 --> 00:40:55.076
Which means more Zoners on Earth.

523
00:40:56.420 --> 00:40:57.648
You find the one in India?

524
00:40:58.189 --> 00:41:02.023
That was just a smoking hole.
But I did find another one in Australia...

525
00:41:02.193 --> 00:41:03.854
...that you might wanna look at.

526
00:41:07.965 --> 00:41:09.398
Is there someone in the crater?

527
00:41:11.735 --> 00:41:15.466
I blew it up as much as I could.
It's not very clear. but...

528
00:41:24.448 --> 00:41:25.676
What is it?

529
00:41:30.454 --> 00:41:31.478
Raya.

530
00:41:32.305 --> 00:42:32.660
